 E[H(X)] = \frac{E[R]}{E[r]}. (4.23)
H(X) = R/r
 E[H(X)] = \frac{E[R]}{E[r]}
H(X) = R/r
 \frac{E[R]}{E[r]} = \frac{E[\sum_{t=0}^{r - 1} H(X_t)]}{E[r]} =  \frac{E[ E(\sum_{t=0}^{T - 1} H(X_t) | r=T)]}{E[r]} =  \frac{E[ r E(H(X))]}{E[r]} = E(H(X)). 
